<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910926-0081</DOCNO><DOCID>910926-0081.</DOCID><HL>   U.S., British Regulators   Sign Pact on Securities Data</HL><DATE>09/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12</SO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>SECURITIES REGULATIONS AND ENFORCEMENT (RGU)SECURITIES (SCR)</IN><NS>SECURITIES REGULATION (RGU)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   WASHINGTON -- British and U.S. securities and futuresregulators signed an accord to expand the information flowbetween the countries.   The agreement, signed at a meeting of internationalregulators, is designed to improve cooperation in possiblefraud cases, failure to properly report positions and otherpotential illegalities in the securities and futures markets.</LP><TEXT>   The agencies said the agreement, which supersedes asimilar five-year-old accord, directs regulators to assisttheir counterparts by providing access to information alreadyin the files, questioning individuals designated by therequesting country, and obtaining documents from individuals.   The pact also directs the regulators to conduct complianceinspections and allow representatives of the requestingcountry to participate in inquiries.</TEXT></DOC>